{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a2024cb3-f1b9-4911-8e69-9fb7db862401","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LW5exGSYoyeh4xrtZz8AoW","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VARrrnk7CmdoWNHuzsqfjk","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-25b8288984c34fc49ffcaa008590dc9c && dotnet nuget list source 2>/dev/null; dotnet --version 2>/dev/null","description":"Check dotnet and nuget config","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check dotnet and nuget config"}],"interactionId":"4c8a43b3-d89c-4bd9-96af-50c1958092e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **Project file changes:**\n   - Replace `xunit` v2 package with `xunit.v3` v3 package\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't use it - projects are executables)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n   - Change SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (actually v3 uses exe output type)\n   - Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since xUnit v3 test projects are executables\n   - Target framework like net8.0 should work fine\n\n2. **Test code changes:**\n   - `async void` test methods are no longer allowed in v3 - must change to `async Task`\n   - The `using Xunit;` namespace stays the same\n\n3. **global.json and runner changes:**\n   - v3 uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` runner instead of VSTest, so the test runner configuration needs updating\n\nLet me verify the exact xUnit v3 migration requirements to make sure I'm covering all the necessary changes.\n\nFor xUnit v3, the key differences are:\n- The NuGet package is `xunit.v3` instead of `xunit`\n- Test projects need to be configured as executables rather than class libraries\n- `async void` tests aren't supported anymore - they must be `async Task`\n- The built-in runner based on Microsoft.Testing.Platform handles test execution\n- You'll use `dotnet test` with the new runner\n\nNow I'm checking what the current xUnit v3 package version is - it should be around 1.0.0 since v3 restarted the version numbering, and `async void` tests need to become `async Task`.\n\nFor the global.json configuration, I should either remove the test runner specification entirely since xUnit v3 embeds its own runner, or update it to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me go ahead and make these changes to the project files and see if it builds correctly.","outputTokens":983,"requestId":"0428:1300AE:33D8B6:3D6E5F:69E824A4"},"id":"35193670-07bd-443c-8a7b-511e6ba3c8c0","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:30:34.710Z","parentId":"ee498080-5cd0-4f3e-862f-9d2116dde593"}
